# Udemy Course Finder — Implementation Plan

A self-hosted web application that scrapes 9 coupon websites for free, English-language Udemy courses, deduplicates them into a searchable catalog, and serves them through a modern dashboard with source management, analytics, favorites, and history — all running via Docker Compose.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tech Stack Confirmation**: The ARU specifies **Next.js 15 + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui** for the frontend. Since the general coding guidelines prefer vanilla CSS, but the ARU explicitly mandates Tailwind, **the ARU takes precedence**. Please confirm this is acceptable.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Phase 1 Scope Only**: This plan covers **Phase 1** (core infrastructure) as defined in Section 17 of the ARU. Phases 2–4 will be planned separately after Phase 1 is complete and validated.

> [!WARNING]
> **No Actual Scraping in Phase 1**: The scraper engine (Python) is Phase 2. In Phase 1, we scaffold the backend, DB, auth, and frontend shell. The scraper worker container will be defined in Docker Compose but will be a placeholder.

