## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Deduplication Key**: The ARU (Section 19) flags this as unresolved. I recommend using a **composite key of `udemy_course_id` (extracted from URL) + `provider_id`** for uniqueness within a source, and `udemy_course_id` alone for cross-source dedup. If the Udemy course ID can't always be extracted, we fall back to normalized title matching. **Please confirm or provide your preferred strategy.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Scrape Schedule Cadence**: Not specified in ARU. I recommend **every 30 minutes** as default (configurable in `settings` table) given coupon expiry windows of 24–72 hours. **Please confirm or specify your preferred interval.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3 — Multi-User in Phase 1?**: The ARU says "single technical user" but the schema supports multiple. I recommend **single default admin user (seeded)** in Phase 1, with multi-user deferred to Phase 4. **Please confirm.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q4 — Category Taxonomy**: Fixed list or derived from scraped data? I recommend a **hybrid**: seed with Udemy's official categories (Development, Business, IT & Software, etc.) and allow scrapers to create new categories if they encounter unknown ones. **Please confirm.**

