#### [NEW] [schema.prisma](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/backend/prisma/schema.prisma)
Full database schema implementing Section 8 of the ARU:

| Table | Key Design Decisions |
|---|---|
| `users` | Argon2 hash field, `role` enum (ADMIN, USER), timestamps |
| `courses` | Composite unique on `udemy_course_id` for cross-source dedup; `provider_id` FK; full-text search index on `title` + `description`; `is_active` + `expires_at` compound index |
| `providers` | All 9 sources seeded; `is_enabled`, `timeout_ms`, `last_run_at`, `last_status` |
| `categories` | `name` + `slug` unique; seeded with Udemy official categories |
| `favorites` | Unique constraint on `(user_id, course_id)` |
| `history` | `action` enum (VIEWED, CLICKED, ENROLLED) |
| `logs` | Per-provider run logs with `job_id`, `status`, `message`, timing |
| `settings` | Key-value store for app config |

#### [NEW] [seed.ts](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/backend/prisma/seed.ts)
- Create default admin user (email/password from `.env`)
- Seed all 9 providers with names, base URLs, enabled by default
- Seed ~15 Udemy official categories

#### [NEW] Auth Module
- `POST /auth/login` — validate credentials, return access + refresh JWT tokens
- `POST /auth/refresh` — rotate refresh token
- `POST /auth/logout` — invalidate refresh token (blacklist in Redis)
- JWT strategy using Passport with configurable expiry
- Argon2 password hashing via `argon2` npm package
- Rate limiting on auth endpoints (throttler)

#### [NEW] Courses Module
- `GET /courses` — paginated list with filters (category, provider, expiry status, sort)
- `GET /courses/:id` — full detail
- `GET /courses/search` — full-text search with query params
- Repository pattern: `CoursesRepository` wraps all Prisma calls
- Redis caching for expensive queries (list, search) with TTL

#### [NEW] Providers Module
- `GET /providers` — list all with status/stats
- `PATCH /providers/:id` — enable/disable, update timeout
- `POST /providers/scrape` — enqueue manual scrape job (BullMQ stub)
- `POST /providers/:id/test` — dry-run connectivity check (stub)
- `POST /providers/:id/retry` — retry failed job (stub)
- `GET /providers/:id/logs` — paginated logs
- `GET /providers/:id/stats` — aggregate stats

#### [NEW] Favorites Module
- `GET /favorites` — user's favorites (with course details, expired flag)
- `POST /favorites` — add to favorites (idempotent)
- `DELETE /favorites/:courseId` — remove from favorites

#### [NEW] History Module
- `GET /history` — user's click/view history (paginated)
- `POST /history` — record a view/click event

#### [NEW] Analytics Module (Stub)
- `GET /analytics/overview` — returns placeholder data in Phase 1; real implementation in Phase 4

#### [NEW] Backend Dockerfile
- Multi-stage build: install deps → build → production image
- Node 20 Alpine base
- Prisma generate + migrate on startup

